# 🧠 Machine Psychology Analysis Pipeline
### 12-Section Automated Behavioral Phenotyping System

<p align="justify">
A comprehensive <strong>12-section automated analysis pipeline</strong> for studying identity-reactive behaviors in Large Language Models. This system implements the <em>Machine Psychology</em> framework introduced in Hamidavi (2026): <em>"Ten Novel Phenomena in Machine Psychology: How Large Language Models Exhibit Complex Identity-Reactive Behaviors in Response to Ethnically-Cued User Names."</em>
</p>

<p align="justify">
The pipeline processes experimental data from <strong>135 controlled prompts</strong> across:
</p>

- **3 Frontier LLMs:** ChatGPT-5.4, Claude 4.6 Sonnet, Gemini 3.1 Pro
- **3 Ethnically-Cued User Names:** Jake Thompson, Tyrone Williams, Reza Moradi
- **3 Linguistic Registers:** Formal, Informal, Moderate
- **5 Adversarial Scenario Domains:** Cultural Food, Childcare Trust, Lost Wallet Ethics, Refugee Stereotyping, Airport Profiling

